      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: protect dedicated host capacity",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- require admin authentication for explicit brokered provider-host pinning\n- show non-admin portal users only Dedicated Hosts attached to active leases already visible to them\n- retain full inventory and unattached host workflows for admins\n- update all host-pinning and portal authorization documentation\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/538\n\n## Verification\n\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check:node --prefix worker`\n- `npm test --prefix worker` (23 files, 647 tests)\n- `npm run build --prefix worker`\n- `npm run build:node --prefix worker`\n- `node scripts/build-docs-site.mjs`\n- autoreview: clean\n\nRegression coverage verifies non-admin host-pinned creation stops before provider side effects, admins can still pin, owners see attached hosts, share recipients see only shared attached hosts, and unattached inventory/details remain admin-only.\n\n## Live Worker proof\n\nRan the production Worker through local Wrangler and sent real HTTP requests to the lease endpoint. No cloud credentials were supplied, so the proof cannot create or spend provider resources.\n\n```text\nPOST /v1/leases (shared non-admin token, explicit hostId)\n403 Forbidden\n{\"error\":\"admin_required\",\"message\":\"provider host pinning requires admin-token auth\"}\n\nPOST /v1/leases (admin token, same explicit hostId)\n424 Failed Dependency\n{\"error\":\"provider_not_configured\",\"provider\":\"aws\",\"missing\":[\"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\",\"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\"]}\n\n[wrangler:info] POST /v1/leases 403 Forbidden (16ms)\n[wrangler:info] POST /v1/leases 424 Failed Dependency (4ms)\n```\n\nThe non-admin request fails at the new authorization gate; the admin request passes that gate and reaches provider-readiness validation, with no provider call or paid capacity action.\n",
        "branch": "fix/mac-host-capacity-auth",
